Four suspects were arrested and  about R70,000 worth of suspected stolen tyres recovered in Deal Party, Gqeberha, on Monday evening. Police spokesperson Captain Sandra Janse van Rensburg said  Mount Road police were patrolling in Old Grahamstown Road,  Deal Party,  at about  7.30pm, when they noticed a white Colt  bakkie driving without lights towards Swartkops. “Two men were seen lying on a big load that was covered with a tent at the back of the bakkie. “The  officers stopped the vehicle and on searching the vehicle, 22 different sizes of tyres were found. “The suspects were unable to provide any information or proof of purchase. “The tyres are  valued at about R70,000. Their vehicle was also impounded.” All four suspects, aged between 24 and 33, face  charges of possession of  stolen goods. Janse van Rensburg said   the suspects would  appear in the Gqeberha magistrate’s court soon. HeraldLIVE  